### Which @angular/* package(s) are the source of the bug?

core, common

### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

When inserting an embedded view from a prepared `TemplateRef`, which in turn inserts another embedded view from a prepared `TemplateRef` with an `@let` declaration inside, it leads to an error `Expecting instance of DOM Element`. Without hydration, no error occurs.

Steps to reproduce:

1. app.config.ts
```typescript
export const appConfig: ApplicationConfig = {
  providers: [
    provideClientHydration(withEventReplay()),
    provideZoneChangeDetection({ eventCoalescing: true }),
    provideRouter(appRoutes),
  ],
};
```
2. app.component.ts
```typescript
@Component({
  imports: [NgTemplateOutlet, TemplateContainerComponent],
  selector: 'app-root',
  template: `
    <app-template-container #tmplContainer />

    <ng-container [ngTemplateOutlet]="tmplContainer.tmplContainerRef()" />
  `,
})
export class AppComponent {}
```
3. template-container.component.ts
```typescript
@Component({
  imports: [NgTemplateOutlet, TemplateComponent],
  selector: 'app-template-container',
  template: `
    <app-template #tmpl />

    <ng-template #tmplContainer>
      <ng-container [ngTemplateOutlet]="tmpl.tmplRef()" />
    </ng-template>
  `,
})
export class TemplateContainerComponent {
  tmplContainerRef = viewChild.required<TemplateRef<unknown>>('tmplContainer');
}

```
4. template.component.ts
```typescript
@Component({
  selector: 'app-template',
  template: `
    <ng-template #tmpl>
      @let a = 'error occurs here';

      {{ a }}
    </ng-template>
  `,
})
export class TemplateComponent {
  tmplRef = viewChild.required<TemplateRef<unknown>>('tmpl');
}
```

The error will appear on startup.

