If you have something simple like this:

Entry `.css` file:
```css
@import "./tailwind-dependencies.css";
@layer components { };
```

... where `tailwind-dependencies.css` is:
```css
@tailwind base;
@tailwind components;
@tailwind utilities;
```

Trying to build gives this error:
```
X [ERROR] `@layer components` is used but no matching `@tailwind components` directive is present. [plugin angular-css]
```

... because PostCSS (with the PostCSS "Tailwind CSS" plugin) runs first.

What I'm expecting is for the esbuild CSS loader, to build the ONE CSS file, and then run PostCSS (with the PostCSS "Tailwind CSS" plugin) on that.

Does that make sense?

